<p>Kudos on exposing the defeatist elements in the Computer Science curriculum. I&#8217;ve never understood why the dogma of the software with bugs thing is so universally accepted. I think it comes from the book The Mythical Man-Moth which I had to read in College and you probably will too.</p>

<p>I guess it&#8217;s reasonable to assume that there will be bugs in a very large project, but this book argues that the first incantation of a software will be so infested that it has to be thrown out.</p>

